File: MTN office in Morningside. eNCA JOHANNESBURG - MTN South Africa grew its subscriber base by 7.1 percent at the end of March to reach 34.5 million subscribers. It's seen good performance in both prepaid and contracts. READ: MTN says crackdown on unregistered phones won't impact finances The network operator says it also saw a group double-digit service revenue growth despite a challenging macro-economic environment. The company says power cuts in South Africa have impacted network availability. As a result, it has had to increase investment in batteries ahead of the winter period as it anticipates that the risk of power cuts may remain high.